OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FNo school dinners if       
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fchild's debt is 2p, Gwynedd
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fhead says                  
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Pupils will not be allowed school meals
OL,6, if they are more than a penny in debt, 
OL,7, according to a letter to parents.      
OL,9,FThe cook at secondary Ysgol Dyffryn    
OL,10,FNantlle, in Penygroes, Gwynedd, has    
OL,11,Fbeen "instructed not to give food to   
OL,12,Fany child" if debts are not cleared.   
OL,14,FStrategic head teacher Neil Foden's    
OL,15,Fletter said the decision was due to a  
OL,16,Fdeficit in the school meals budget.    
OL,18,FGwynedd council said anyone "having    
OL,19,Fdifficulty" paying for school meals    
OL,20,Fshould get in touch.                   
